The fragment as written does not call MHD_DLOG itself (no direct recursion) and does not statically call any function that in the shown code calls MHD_DLOG (no evident indirect recursion). Therefore the fragment does not by itself violate Rule 17.2. A concrete violation scenario would be if daemon->custom_error_log were implemented so that it (directly or indirectly) calls MHD_DLOG again — for example: 

void my_error_log(void *cls, const char *fmt, va_list va) {
  /* build message */
  MHD_DLOG((struct MHD_Daemon *)cls, "%s", msg); /* indirect recursion: MHD_DLOG -> my_error_log -> MHD_DLOG */
}

If custom_error_log points to such a function (or to any function that leads back to MHD_DLOG), then an indirect recursion would occur and Rule 17.2 would be violated.
